Session.Read(name) returns the bytes of .drift/&lt;name&gt;. A missing file returns an error for which os.IsNotExist reports true (callers use this to distinguish "fresh project" from "corrupt state"). Read does not take the lock per-call; it relies on the lock held since Begin. Read is safe for any file under .drift/ — state.xml, baselines.bin, user-settings.xml, theme.xml, .gitignore.